Ten suspects have been apprehended so far after in connection with four men who were stabbed to death. CAPE TOWN - Police say further arrests will be made in connection with a mob attack in which four men were stabbed to death in the Eastern Cape.Ten suspects have been apprehended so far and will appear in the Libode magistrates court on Friday.It's believed that they were killed after being linked to stock theft.The police's Mzukisi Fatyela said: The investigation led to the arrest of 10 people, aged between 20 and 47, and they were arrested in the same area as where the murder of those four people happened. 